{{Chinese name|[[Cheng (surname)|Cheng]]}}
'''Cheng Yuan''' ({{zh|s=成源|p=Chéng Yuán}}; born 8 October 1993 in [[Jinan]]) is a [[Chinese people|Chinese]] footballer who plays for [[Shandong Luneng Taishan F.C.|Shandong Luneng Taishan]] in the [[Chinese Super League]].

==Club career==
Cheng Yuan began his football career in 2011 when he was promoted to [[Shandong Province Youth Football Team|Shandong Youth]]'s squad for the [[2011 China League Two]] campaign. He spent two season in Shandong Youth, scoring nines goals in thirty-two appearances. In September 2013, he was loaned to [[Segunda Liga]] side [[S.C. Covilhã]] until the end of 2013/14 season.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mercado: OFICIAL - Avançado e médio chineses reforçam plantel do Covilhã |url=http://www.futebol365.pt/noticia/92918/ |publisher=futebol365.net|date=3 September 2013|accessdate=3 May 2014}}</ref> On 23 October 2013, he made his debut for Covilhã in a league match against [[Sporting Clube de Portugal B|Sporting CP B]] where he coming on as a substitute for [[Tiago Jorge Oliveira Lopes|Tiago Lopes]] in the 86th minute.<ref>{{cite web|title=SPORTING COVILHÃ VS. SPORTING CP II  0 - 2 |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2013/10/23/portugal/liga-de-honra/sc-covilha/sporting-b/1512307/ |publisher=soccerway|accessdate=3 May 2014}}</ref>

Cheng returned to Shandong and was promoted to first team squad by [[Cuca (footballer)|Cuca]] in the summer of 2014. On 13 May 2015, he made his debut for Shandong in a [[2015 Chinese FA Cup]] against amateur team Wuhan New Era, coming on as a substitute for [[Zheng Zheng]] in the 65th minute.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://sports.163.com/15/0513/17/APGTN0J600051C89.html |title=足协杯-杨旭2球韩鹏破门 鲁能6-1胜业余队进16强 |publisher=netease |date=13 May 2015 |accessdate=17 November 2016}}</ref> He made his [[Chinese Super League]] debut on 20 June 2015 in a 2–1 home defeat against [[Guangzhou Evergrande Taobao F.C.|Guangzhou Evergrande]], coming on for Zheng Zheng in the 82nd minute.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://sports.sina.com.cn/china/j/2015-06-20/doc-ifxefurq9085618.shtml|title=中超-郑龙传射 斯帅开门红恒大2-1鲁能登榜首 |publisher=Sina |date=20 June 2015 |accessdate=17 November 2016}}</ref> Although failing to establish himself within the senior team, Cheng was the highest goalscorer with a new record of 23 goals in the 2015 Chinese Super League reserve league.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://sports.sohu.com/20151104/n425182680.shtml|title=鲁能预备队射手王或离队 高准翼有望租借赴延边 |publisher=Sohu |date=4 November 2015 |accessdate=17 November 2016}}</ref> He was demoted to the reserve squad in July 2016 after [[Felix Magath]] became the manager of the club. He defended the title of highest goalscorer in the 2016 Chinese Super League reserve league with 20 goals.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://sports.sohu.com/20161031/n471853152.shtml|title=鲁能预备队2-4不敌恒大 成源轰20球荣膺射手王 |publisher=Sohu |date=31 October 2016 |accessdate=17 November 2016}}</ref> On 2 May 2017, he scored his first and second goal for the club in the [[2017 Chinese FA Cup]] as Shandong Luneng beat China League Two club [[Jilin Baijia F.C.|Jilin Baijia]] 4–1.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://sports.sina.com.cn/china/cfacup/2017-05-02/doc-ifyetwtf9565966.shtml|title=足协杯-成源2球李松益崔巍破门 鲁能4-1轻松晋级|publisher=Sina |date=2 May 2017 |accessdate=3 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://sports.sina.com.cn/china/cfacup/2017-05-02/doc-ifyetwtf9579609.shtml |title=别再管他叫小将成源 24岁的前锋这称谓就是讽刺 |publisher=Sina |date=2 May 2017 |accessdate=3 May 2017}}</ref> He won the top goalscorer of Chinese Super League reserve league for the third time in 2017, scoring 24 goals in the season.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://sports.sina.com.cn/china/j/2017-11-07/doc-ifynmzrs7742210.shtml |title=2017中超预备队联赛总结 各队空前重视竞争激烈 |publisher=Sina |date=7 November 2017 |accessdate=9 November 2017}}</ref>

